cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.CC, cs.DM, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the complexity of infinite computations in models of set theory, which is a topic closely related to mathematical logic. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the complexity of languages recognized by automata. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper deals with the complexity of decision problems. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with the theory of infinite sets and languages. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the theory of automata and languages, which is relevant to programming language theory.
